    • Method Detail

      • get

        Rule get(String hlid)
  throws KbTypeException,
         CreateException
        Get the Rule that corresponds to hlid. Throws exceptions if the hlid doesn't correspond to an object in the KB, or if the object identified by hlid is not an assertion with an #$implies operator.

        NOTE: Most of the get (String) factory methods in other classes find objects based on hlids or string representations of the object. They use nameOrId as the string variable name. This method finds objects based on hlid alone. If you want to find a rule based on its string representation, try using get(java.lang.String, java.lang.String).

        Specified by:
        get in interface AssertionService
        Parameters:
        hlid - the hlid corresponding to the Rule in the KB
        Returns:
        a Rule based on hlid
        Throws:
        KbTypeException - if assertion based on hlid is not an instance of assertion with #$implies operator
        CreateException
        See Also:
        AssertionService.get(com.cyc.kb.Sentence, com.cyc.kb.Context), AssertionService.get(java.lang.String, java.lang.String)

      • findOrCreate

        Rule findOrCreate(String formulaStr)
           throws CreateException,
                  KbTypeException,
                  InvalidFormulaInContextException
        Finds or creates the Rule that corresponds to formulaStr in the default assertion context. Tries to assert if no rule with that formula can be found in that context. Throws an exception if it is unable to create the rule in the KB. Strength is set to Strength.DEFAULT by default. Direction is set to Direction.BACKWARD by default.
        Specified by:
        findOrCreate in interface AssertionService
        Parameters:
        formulaStr - the string representation of the rule to be found or created
        Returns:
        a Rule based on formulaStr in the default assertion context
        Throws:
        CreateException
        KbTypeException
        InvalidFormulaInContextException - if no assertion with the given formula can be found or created in the context
